parameters: \nc<>Well, well, both of you are working hard again today.
\nc<>Being here means you're serving the believers, right?

\nc<>It's just for the sake of the Rakuenkyo, you
know.
There's nothing else to it...

\nc<>It's unlikely that two pure-hearted individuals like you
would spread your legs without being in charge of serving,
right?

\nc<>However, I'm sorry. Right now, the service room is under
renovation.

\nc<>Thanks to the recent active participation of both of you,
the number of people in Rakuenkyo has increased
significantly.

\nc<>You're saying strange things. Wouldn't it be better if you
contributed in other ways?

\nc<>(Hehe, you have such a blatantly disappointed
expression.)
(Even righteous magical girls end up like
this when they indulge in carnal desires.)

\nc<>(Well, fine. The depth of hypnosis has reached its
limit.)
(There is no reason to stop what the person
desires.)

\nc<>That's right. By the way, I heard that the enthusiasm of
the believers has significantly decreased since the service
room went under renovation.

\nc<>Th-that's not good.
We need to resolve it urgently.

\nc<>Therefore, I would like both of you to take on the temporary
role of permanent service executives. Is that okay?

\ncExcuse me, but what kind of work does the permanent service
executive do?

\nc<>The most important thing is to immediately purify the
accumulated impurities when there is a request from the
believers.
\nc<>While I'm in the Paradise Church, always.

\nc<>To think that we have to purify immediately when there is a
request... that's...
\nc<>Do... do I have the right to refuse?

\nc<>(...Why does hearing this make me feel better?) (The
thoughts of a pervert... truly.)

\nc<>I am aware that it is a difficult task. However, if it's not
the two of you, there is no one else I can rely on.
\nc<Sachiko>Y-Yes. If it's what the Founder says...

\nc<>If it's for the Paradise Church, there's no other choice,
right?
If it's for the Paradise Church.

\nc<>Now then, please put on that necklace right away and start
your mission.
